Sam
saw
the
sense
in
the
decree,
but
he
hated
longbow
practice
almost
as
much
as
he
hated
climbing
steps.
When
he
wore
his
gloves
he
could
never
hit
anything,
but
when
he
took
them
off
he
got
blisters
on
his
fingers.
Those
bows
were
dangerous.
Satin
had
torn
off
half
his
thumbnail
on
a
bowstring.
“I
forgot.”

“You
broke
the
heart
of
the
wildling
princess,
Slayer,”
said
Pyp.
Of
late,
Val
had
taken
to
watching
them
from
the
window
of
her
