“Mother.”
Tommen
tugged
her
sleeve.
“What
smells
so
bad?”

My
lord
father.
“Death.”
She
could
smell
it
too;
a
faint
whisper
of
decay
that
made
her
want
to
wrinkle
her
nose.
Cersei
paid
it
no
mind.
The
seven
septons
in
the
silver
