“And
what
have
you
discovered?”

“The
night
that
Lord
Varys
and
your
brother
disappeared,
a
third
man
also
vanished.”

“Yes,
the
gaoler.
What
of
him?”

“Rugen
was
the
man’s
name.
An
undergaoler
who
had
charge
of
the
black
cells.
The
chief
undergaoler
describes
him
as
portly,
unshaven,
gruff
