no
kin.
Nor
did
he
drink
or
frequent
brothels.
His
sleeping
cell
was
damp
and
dreary,
and
the
straw
he
slept
upon
was
mildewed.
His
chamber
pot
was
overflowing.”

“I
know
all
this.”
Jaime
had
examined
Rugen’s
cell,
and
Ser
Addam’s
gold
cloaks
had
examined
it
again.

“Aye,
Your
Grace,”
said
Qyburn,
“but
did
you
