of
blood
and
death.
“What
did
you
imagine
you
were
doing?”

“No
more’n
we
was
told,
my
lord.”
Ser
Boros
was
shorter
than
Jaime,
but
heavier.
“Her
Grace
commanded
it.
Your
sister.”

Ser
Osmund
hooked
a
thumb
through
his
swordbelt.
“She
said
they
were
to
sleep
forever.
So
my
brothers
and
me,
we
saw
to
it.”

That
you
did.
One
corpse
sprawled
facedown
upon
the
table,
like
a
man
passed
out
at
a
feast,
but
it
was
a
puddle
of
blood
beneath
his
head,
not
a
puddle
of
wine.
The
second
turnkey
had
managed
to
push
back
from
the
bench
and
draw
his
dagger
before
someone
shoved
a
longsword
through
