looking
on
in
place
of
the
thousands
who
had
seen
his
brother
joined
to
the
same
woman.

The
bride
was
fair
and
gay
and
beautiful,
the
groom
still
baby-faced
and
plump.
He
recited
his
vows
in
a
high,
childish
voice,
promising
his
love
and
devotion
to
Mace
Tyrell’s
twice-widowed
daughter.
Margaery
wore
the
same
gown
she
had
worn
to
