to
her
knees
and
Tommen
covered
her
with
the
heavy
cloth-of-gold
monstrosity
that
Robert
had
cloaked
Cersei
in
on
their
own
wedding
day,
with
the
crowned
stag
of
Baratheon
worked
upon
its
back
in
beads
of
onyx.
Cersei
had
wanted
to
use
the
fine
red
silk
cloak
Joffrey
had
used.
“It
was
the
cloak
my
lord
father
used
when
he
wed
my
lady
mother,”
she
explained
to
the
Tyrells,
but
the
Queen
of
Thorns
had
balked
