voice
said,
“To
the
king
and
queen!”
The
other
sheep
all
baaaaaaed
along
with
him.
“The
king
and
queen!”
they
cried,
smashing
their
cups
together.
“The
king
and
queen!”
She
had
no
choice
but
to
drink
along
with
them,
all
the
time
wishing
that
the
guests
had
but
a
single
face,
so
she
could
throw
her
wine
into
their
eyes
and
remind
them
that
she
was
the
true
queen.
The
only
one
of
Tyrell’s
lickspittles
who
seemed
to
remember
her
at
all
was
Paxter
Redwyne,
who
rose
to
make
his
own
