“Winter
is
coming,”
Arya
whispered.

“The
hard
cruel
times,”
her
father
said.
“We
tasted
them
on
the
Trident,
child,
and
when
Bran
fell.
You
were
born
in
the
long
summer,
sweet
one,
you’ve
never
