on
a
wall
peg
next
to
Jaime’s.

“I
saw
you
in
the
yard
today,”
said
Jaime.
“You
rode
well.”

“Better
than
well,
surely.”
Ser
Loras
poured
himself
a
cup
of
wine,
and
took
a
seat
across
the
half-moon
table.

“A
more
modest
man
might
have
answered
‘My
lord
is
too
