Lady
Sansa,”
said
Pycelle.

The
queen
bristled.
“I
most
certainly
have
not
forgotten
that
little
she-wolf.”
She
refused
to
say
the
girl’s
name.
“I
ought
to
have
shown
her
to
the
black
cells
as
the
daughter
of
a
traitor,
but
instead
I
made
her
part
of
mine
own
