on
the
breast.
The
king’s
own
brother
had
gone
with
him
to
help
choose
the
design,
the
potboy
said.
No,
not
Lord
Renly,
the
other
one,
Lord
Stannis.

“Did
our
watchman
recall
anything
else
of
note?”

“The
lad
swears
Lord
Jon
was
as
strong
as
a
man
half
his
age.
Often
went
riding
with
Lord
Stannis,
he
says.”

Stannis
again,
Ned
thought.
He
found
that
curious.
Jon
Arryn
and
he
had
been
cordial,
but
never
friendly.
And
while
Robert
had
been
riding
north
to
Winterfell,
Stannis
had
removed
himself
to
Dragonstone,
the
Targaryen
island
fastness
he
had
conquered
in
his
brother’s
name.
He
had
given
no
word
as
