earth.
A
broken
sword
was
in
his
hand,
but
it
was
his
face
that
gave
her
pause,
the
small
eyes
and
wide
flat
nostrils.

She
knew
that
nose.
She
knew
those
eyes.
Pyg,
his
friends
had
called
him.

Everything
seemed
to
happen
in
a
heartbeat.
A
second
man
slipped
over
the
lip
of
the
well,
making
no
more
