He
swung
it
hard
and
low,
and
one
of
Crabb’s
knees
exploded
in
a
spray
of
blood
and
bone.
“That’s
funny,”
Shagwell
crowed
as
Dick
fell.
The
sword
she’d
given
him
went
flying
from
his
hand
and
vanished
in
the
weeds.
He
writhed
on
the
ground,
screaming
and
clutching
at
the
ruins
of
his
knee.
“Oh,
look,”
said
Shagwell,
“it’s
Smuggler
Dick,
the
one
who
made
the
map
for
us.
Did
you
come
all
this
way
to
give
us
back
our
gold?”

“Please,”
Dick
whimpered,
“please
don’t,
my
leg...”

“Does
it
hurt?
I
can
make
it
stop.”

“Leave
him
be,”
said
Brienne.

“DON’T!”
shrieked
Dick,
lifting
bloody
hands
to
shield
