Brienne
snorted.
“As
if
you
could.”

“What
will
you
do
now,
my
lady?”

“Cover
him.”

“About
the
girl,
I
meant.
The
Lady
Sansa.”

Brienne
thought
a
moment.
“She
was
making
for
Riverrun,
if
Timeon
told
it
true.
Somewhere
along
the
way
she
was
taken
by
the
Hound.
If
I
find
him...”

“...he’ll
kill
you.”

“Or
I’ll
kill
him,”
she
said
stubbornly.
“Will
you
help
me
cover
up
poor
Crabb,
ser?”

“No
true
knight
could
refuse
such
