sharpening
his
steel,
but
she
had
looked
at
them
from
a
closer
vantage
and
she
knew
that
they
were
purple.
Dark
purple.
Dark
and
angry.

He
must
have
felt
her
gaze
upon
him,
for
he
looked
up
from
his
sword,
met
