“Often
and
loudly,”
she
agreed.
“No
doubt
your
friends
will
ride
that
way
when
they
come
after
us.
I
wish
them
good
speed.”

Even
now,
long
days
later,
the
memory
filled
him
with
a
bitter
rage.
All
his
life
Tyrion
had
prided
himself
on
his
cunning,
the
only
gift
the
gods
had
seen
fit
to
give
him,
and
yet
this
seven-times-damned
she-wolf
Catelyn
Stark
had
outwitted
him
at
every
turn.
The
knowledge
was
more
galling
than
the
bare
fact
of
his
abduction.

They
stopped
only
as
long
as
it
took
to
feed
and
water
the
