they
scarcely
bothered
to
guard
him
at
all.
It
seemed
they
did
not
fear
his
escape.
And
why
should
they?
Up
here
the
land
was
harsh
and
wild,
and
the
high
road
little
more
than
a
stony
track.
If
he
did
run,
how
far
could
he
hope
to
go,
alone
and
without
