“Yes.
Be
grateful
that
I
have
more
honor
than
some.”
Petyr
sounded
as
angry
as
she
had
ever
heard
him.
“I
have
read
your
declaration
and
heard
your
demands.
Now
hear
mine.
Remove
your
armies
from
this
mountain.
Go
home
and
leave
my
son
in
peace.
Misrule
there
has
been,
I
will
not
