it,
but
that
was
Lysa’s
work,
not
mine.
Grant
me
but
a
year,
and
with
Lord
Nestor’s
help
I
promise
that
none
of
you
shall
have
any
cause
for
grievance.”

“So
you
say,”
said
Belmore.
“Yet
how
shall
we
trust
you?”

“You
dare
call
me
untrustworthy?
It
was
not
me
who
bared
steel
at
a
