time,”
Lord
Redfort
said
uncertainly.
“Mayhaps...
if
you
gave
assurances...”

“None
of
us
wants
war,”
acknowledged
Lady
Waynwood.
“Autumn
wanes,
and
we
must
gird
ourselves
for
winter.”

Belmore
cleared
his
throat.
“At
the
end
of
this
year...”

“...if
I
have
not
set
the
Vale
to
rights,
I
shall
willingly
