Ser
Osmund
shrugged.
“Singers.
She’s
a
fool
for
singers
and
jugglers
and
such.
Knights,
come
round
to
moon
over
her
cousins.
Ser
Tallad’s
the
worst,
Osney
says.
That
big
oaf
don’t
seem
to
know
if
it’s
Elinor
or
Alla
he
wants,
but
he
knows
he
wants
her
awful
bad.
The
Redwyne
twins
come
calling
too.
Slobber
brings
flowers
and
fruit,
and
Horror’s
taken
up
the
lute.
To
hear
Osney
tell
it,
you
could
make
a
sweeter
sound
strangling
a
cat.
The
Summer
Islander’s
always
underfoot
as
