“No,”
Robert
always
told
Xho,
“Next
year,”
though
somehow
next
year
never
came.

“I
couldn’t
say
if
he
was
begging,
Your
Grace,”
Ser
Osmund
answered.
“Osney
says
he’s
teaching
them
the
Summer
Tongue.
Not
Osney,
the
quee—the
filly
and
her
cousins.”

“A
horse
that
speaks
the
Summer
Tongue
would
make
a
great
