The
boy
dropped
the
pitchfork
and
made
a
soft
noise,
something
between
a
gasp
and
a
sigh.
His
hands
closed
around
the
blade.
“Oh,
gods,”
he
moaned,
as
his
undertunic
began
to
redden.
“Take
it
out.”

When
she
took
it
out,
he
died.

The
horses
were
screaming.
Arya
stood
over
the
body,
still
and
frightened
in
the
face
of
death.
Blood
had
gushed
from
the
boy’s
mouth
as
he
collapsed,
and
more
was
seeping
from
the
