“You
have
seen
Ser
Kevan?”

“Aye.
He
passed
here
on
his
way
west.
I
asked
him
to
help
us
take
the
castle,
but
Kevan
would
have
none
of
it.
He
brooded
the
whole
time
he
was
here.
Courteous
enough,
but
chilly.
I
swore
to
him
that
I
never
asked
to
be
made
Warden
of
the
West,
that
the
honor
should
have
gone
to
him,
and
he
declared
