and
stepped
back
two
quick
steps.
He
wrenched
his
axe
up
once
more,
cursing,
and
lurched
after
her,
one
foot
sliding
in
the
mud...

...and
she
leapt
to
meet
his
rush,
both
hands
on
her
sword
