His
axe
fell
from
limp
fingers,
and
the
two
of
them
slammed
together,
Brienne’s
face
mashed
up
against
the
dog’s
head
helm.
She
felt
the
cold
wet
metal
against
her
cheek.
Rain
ran
down
the
steel
in
rivers,
and
when
the
lightning
flashed
again
she
saw
pain
and
fear
and
rank
