the
mud.
One
of
his
hands
was
in
her
hair,
pulling
her
head
back.
The
other
groped
for
her
throat.
Oathkeeper
was
gone,
torn
from
her
grasp.
She
had
only
her
hands
to
fight
him
off,
but
when
she
slammed
a
fist
into
his
face
it
was
like
punching
a
ball
of
wet
white
dough.
He
hissed
at
her.

She
hit
him
again,
again,
again,
smashing
the
heel
of
her
hand
into
his
eye,
but
he
did
not
seem
to
feel
her
