where
she
scratched
him.
He
was
crushing
her,
smothering
her.
She
pushed
at
his
shoulders
to
get
him
off
her,
but
he
was
heavy
as
a
horse,
impossible
to
move.
When
she
tried
to
knee
him
in
the
groin,
all
she
did
was
drive
her
knee
into
his
belly.
Grunting,
Biter
tore
out
a
handful
of
her
hair.

My
dagger.
Brienne
clutched
at
the
thought,
desperate.
She
worked
her
hand
down
between
them,
fingers
squirming
under
his
sour,
